All the dependent packages are included in the release for users convenience.
The dependent packages will be installed to /usr/local, you need to have the
permission to install code in /usr/local directory.  

The release only supports 32-bit linux.

1. Run command "sh ../tools/install.sh /usr/local", 
it will install all dependent packages to /usr/local directory. It is not
recommanded to install dependent packages into a directory other than /usr/local
in this release.  

2. ./configure 

4. make 

5. make install 

6. now you can use mlitecc like gcc to compile your C code. please send bugs at email@ningwang.org


7. compile helloworld.c

#include<stdio.h>
int main () {
   printf ("hello world\n");
   return 0;
}
